[src:pgvector/blob-readme-md] A non-partitioned table has a limit of 32 TB by default in Postgres.
[src:pgvector/blob-readme-md] A partitioned table can have thousands of partitions of that size.
[src:pgvector/blob-readme-md] Yes, pgvector uses the write-ahead log (WAL), which allows for replication and point-in-time recovery.
